content.description: Too obvious to be a new climb but I figured I would add it. Shares a start with The Low Down on slopers, traverse over left but top out straight up at the arete before you get to the dihedral. For full value don’t use the wall to the left of the break.
start on large sloper on right block a few big moves put you into a very awkward move left into a crack continue left into the start for bills monologue finish bills.keep your ass off the rock hahaha
content.location: look at diheadral section start is six feet right around big nose on two slopers

content.description: Start sitting with hands on good holds, use the positive, juggy left facing flake to gain the top. Very fun, easy warmup

start on low jug rail make full expansion move to sloper rail that runs horizontal across most overhung face get match on rail and make a very comitting dyno to a large hold on lip top out straight up . very fun and very hard
content.location: if approaching wall most over hung face.starts on good jug crack about two feet of the ground moves  directly through center of face on the promonate sloper rail . very proud line. easy to find

content.description: Good juggy 12' high,  45 degree overhanging bouldering - There are a number of good lines up to maybe V8-9 and link-ups.
